        public java.io.InputStream openForReading​(ProgressReporter reporter)
        Description copied from interface: Readable
        Opens something that can be read, returning an input stream. The given progress reporter is called for each byte that is read from the input stream. If the input size is known (meaning that Readable.bytes() returns a non-null value), the reporter will be initialized with the number of bytes to allow percent completion to be computed as the stream is read.

      • safeCopyTo

        public void safeCopyTo​(File destination,
                       CopyMode mode,
                       ProgressReporter reporter)
        Copies this readable resource to the given file safely (ensuring that a corrupted copy of the file never exists). This is done by first copying to a temporary file in the same folder. If the copy operation is successful, the destination file is then removed and the temporary file is renamed to the destination file's name.
        Specified by:
        safeCopyTo in interface Resource
        Parameters:
        destination - The file to copy to
